item.title: Whats Happening WIth ScaR!
item.dc:creator: @Iamadam Iamadam
item.description:
@Iamadam wrote:

Usually it does that if you try to access a bitmap that is out of range (or color or whatever). Like trying to do a getColor at (1000, 1000) when the screen targeted is only 768 x 503.
Basically, it tells SCAR - Hey look, get that color there!
Then SCAR goes- Ya, ok! So he tries. And looks in the bitmap stored in memory…
result := pixels[1000][1000];

Noo, pixels[1000][1000] is out of bounds!!! Exception…

Oh, and also make sure that setupSRL has been called, or else you get exceptions left right and center.

Read full topic

item.title: Whats Happening WIth ScaR!
item.dc:creator: @Bebemycat2 Bebe
item.description:
@Bebemycat2 wrote:

Uninstall SCAR and reinstall it.

Also check how the script is coded, some scripts cause SCAR to crash for no reason.

[quote=“DeadBird, post:7, topic:24605”]The script is trying to do something it’s not supposed to, scar stopped it.[/quote]Not True.

If this problem keeps happening then you might consider adding a “Try”/“Except” statement into those set of lines. This will solve the Runtime Error.

[quote=“M0rtion, post:8, topic:24605”]itsgot somyhing to do with bitmaps and dtms…[/quote]Don’t forget to free your bitmaps and DTMs from the memory As that can cause a runtime error.
